title: Japan stocks extend post-election rally with Nikkei 225 breaching 58,000 for the first time
summary_full: Other markets in Asia also shrugged off strong U.S. payrolls data that has dampened expectations for Federal Reserve rate cuts and sent Wall Street lower overnight.
